02:19.170 --> 02:22.401
All right! Oh, that's lovely...

02:22.450 --> 02:23.963
Out the way, mate.

02:25.730 --> 02:27.846
No, Sheila.

02:27.890 --> 02:30.245
Tell me it's not Ground Force?

02:30.290 --> 02:32.167
lt's for the conservatory, Frank!
We're gonna have frosted glass

02:32.210 --> 02:35.919
and blackout blinds for when
l get a bit insidey outsidey.

02:35.970 --> 02:38.928
Hello? The garden's only
ten feet two.

02:38.970 --> 02:40.881
What the fuck we need
a conservatory for?

02:40.930 --> 02:43.160
The wedding!
You know what l'm like,

02:43.210 --> 02:45.883
five hours out here and
l'll go completely doolally.

02:45.930 --> 02:48.125
Well, put up a fucking
wigwam or summat.

02:48.170 --> 02:49.444
Too much daylight.

02:51.050 --> 02:53.086
< How many times, eh?

02:53.130 --> 02:55.690
lf you cold-turkey your tablets,
l need telling

02:55.730 --> 02:59.723
cos A, they're worth money,
B, they're a magnet for every

02:59.770 --> 03:04.480
fucking bronco for miles. How
the hell much is all this costing?

03:04.530 --> 03:05.519
8,000 plus VAT.

03:05.570 --> 03:08.482
Well, we knocked a few quid
off for signing on the spot.

03:08.530 --> 03:11.727
There. There you go.

03:11.770 --> 03:15.399
l said l wanted a conservatory,
Frank! lt's my money.

03:15.450 --> 03:17.441
You haven't got eight grand.

03:17.490 --> 03:18.400
l've got a mortgage.

03:18.450 --> 03:19.599
Three, two, one, back in the room.

03:19.650 --> 03:23.928
Fuck's a re-mortgage costing
me...us...you?

03:23.970 --> 03:26.200
Peanuts, Frank!
Cos l paid off the house last year.

03:26.250 --> 03:28.764
But if l'm gonna be honest,
l missed filing all those bits

03:28.810 --> 03:32.280
of paper they used to send me. So l
took the money out and everything.

03:32.330 --> 03:34.719
l hid it in here.

03:34.770 --> 03:38.319
Well, you always said l
shouldn't let people take advantage.

03:41.250 --> 03:42.399
Come here, you!

03:45.890 --> 03:48.484
God, you are a total one-off!

03:50.730 --> 03:52.800
Why don't you let Frank
take care of that, eh?

03:52.850 --> 03:53.839
OK.

03:55.250 --> 03:58.048
So how much you over-quoted?

03:58.090 --> 03:59.921
Three grand? Four? Let's say four.

03:59.970 --> 04:02.723
Eh? Four grand, split it 50-50.
Gizza receipt for the lot.

04:02.770 --> 04:04.089
Job's eight grand.

04:04.130 --> 04:06.405
On your fucking bike, Tonto!
You seen Watchdog?

04:06.450 --> 04:07.803
Yeah?

04:07.850 --> 04:10.569
Presenter? Sheila's brother. Twins.

04:10.610 --> 04:12.441
He's Scottish.

04:12.490 --> 04:14.242
Phone A Friend or fuck off.

04:15.690 --> 04:20.161
We run an honest business here.
Pay our taxes, all above board.

04:20.209 --> 04:22.519
l've just pulled a cake out
if we're all done and dusted?

04:22.570 --> 04:24.481
Beer, anyone? Gin and tonic?

04:24.530 --> 04:26.964
Nah, l'm all right, thanks, love.
And he's had enough.

04:28.010 --> 04:30.319
Where the fuck did you dig them up?

04:30.370 --> 04:32.281
Advert in the Church Gazette.

04:36.090 --> 04:37.967
Right.

04:38.010 --> 04:41.286
Well, thanks for telling me.

04:41.330 --> 04:43.525
Veronica!

04:43.570 --> 04:46.368
Those tights you gave
me have got a hole in.

04:46.410 --> 04:47.240
Not now, Mum.

04:47.290 --> 04:49.246
Ooh, what's the matter with her?
Lost a fiver, found a...

04:49.290 --> 04:50.803
l said, not now!

04:54.090 --> 04:57.969
l've just found out
me lVF's failed again.

04:58.010 --> 05:00.763
l don't know why you want kids anyway.
Pain in the bloody arse,

05:00.810 --> 05:05.361
if you ask me. Bleed you dry,
take away the best years of your life

05:05.410 --> 05:07.844
and then they grow up
to be a total waste.

05:07.890 --> 05:12.168
Tell you what, Mum, don't mince your
words, say what you really feel.

05:12.210 --> 05:14.883
l mean, it's not much better
from where l'm standing, is it?

05:14.930 --> 05:16.886
l mean, what did l get?

05:16.930 --> 05:18.568
Jane of the fucking jungle.

05:18.610 --> 05:21.283
But with a beard.

05:25.490 --> 05:27.560
Wedding dress. Done.

05:27.610 --> 05:30.761
Order flowers. Done. Wedding cake?

05:30.810 --> 05:33.961
Martha Stewart Berry Basket Cake
with wooden dowel supports, if l can

05:34.010 --> 05:37.719
get the wooden dowels. lf not, l'll
just have to use toilet roll holders.

05:37.770 --> 05:40.443
And you're making that
yourself, so, done! Right,

05:40.490 --> 05:44.085
that brings us to bridesmaids and
you'll obviously want Karen as one.

05:44.130 --> 05:47.247
Me? Bridesmaid? You must be joking!

05:47.290 --> 05:50.805
So that just leaves me,
and Liam as page boy.

05:50.850 --> 05:53.205
l've just had to turn your water
off, love, while we do the digging.

05:53.250 --> 05:54.239
OK.

05:54.290 --> 05:57.521
Right, so that's me and Liam, and l
need a bridesmaid's dress,

05:57.570 --> 05:59.162
so l've found one...

05:59.210 --> 06:01.166
Digging? What does he mean, digging?

06:03.850 --> 06:05.806
But l don't understand.
Why are you digging?

06:05.850 --> 06:07.124
For the foundations!

06:07.170 --> 06:09.604
The ground's solid!
Just put it on there, can't you?

06:09.650 --> 06:12.483
Well, it won't stand up.
We've only gotta dig a few feet.

06:12.530 --> 06:14.646
l said no!
l don't want digging!

06:14.690 --> 06:17.079
But if we don't dig, you
can't have a conservatory.

06:17.130 --> 06:19.121
- All right, just forget it then.
- You what?

06:19.170 --> 06:21.206
l said, forget it.
l don't want a conservatory.

06:21.250 --> 06:22.968
Are you joking or what?
l've booked time in for this job.

06:23.010 --> 06:23.999
And you can't have a refund!

06:24.050 --> 06:27.008
Then keep the money!
And the cake too, if you want it.

06:28.570 --> 06:31.880
Look, l've bought all the gear now!
Let's just get on with it.

06:36.410 --> 06:38.048
Well, that's it then, innit?

06:38.090 --> 06:41.605
No more freebies on the NHS.

06:41.650 --> 06:46.201
And me and Kev sure as shit haven't
got two grand for going private,

06:46.250 --> 06:47.683
so it looks like game over.

06:47.730 --> 06:50.563
ls it still Kev's
sperm that's the problem?

06:50.610 --> 06:52.521
Still doing backstroke.

06:52.570 --> 07:00.124
Thing is, he never wanted 'em, till bloody
mouth almighty started going on about it.

07:00.170 --> 07:01.649
Now he's desperate.

07:03.370 --> 07:05.838
How am l gonna tell him that
they've failed again? l mean...

07:05.890 --> 07:08.927
When they've been hand picked
and scored out of a hundred.

07:08.970 --> 07:14.328
And kids like Mandy Maguire can get
pregnant from just fucking sneezing.

07:14.370 --> 07:15.689
How's that fair?

07:18.970 --> 07:21.006
Have you ever thought
about having any?

07:22.090 --> 07:24.888
Yeah. Dunno...

07:24.930 --> 07:26.409
< Lot of work, aren't they?

07:39.970 --> 07:43.042
< Leave my patio alone!

07:43.090 --> 07:46.366
Leave it alone! Don't make me do this
cos l will!

07:46.410 --> 07:48.640
Hey! What's going on?
Sheila! Sheila!

07:48.690 --> 07:51.568
l don't want it!
l don't want it!

07:51.610 --> 07:53.601
lt's all right. No digging. >

07:53.650 --> 07:56.084
l don't want them to do it.

07:56.130 --> 07:57.643
They won't, they won't.

07:57.690 --> 07:59.328
lt'll be all right, it's all right,
they'll leave it alone.

07:59.370 --> 08:01.247
Fucking hell!

08:02.810 --> 08:04.641
l'm so sorry. l'm so sorry, Frank.

08:04.690 --> 08:07.443
lt's just so awful. lt was so awful.

08:07.490 --> 08:09.128
All right, all right.
There's no need for...

08:09.170 --> 08:12.048
Frank!
There's something l need to tell you.

08:12.090 --> 08:14.684
l can't marry you
without telling you!

08:14.730 --> 08:16.163
You're not a bloke, are you?

08:16.210 --> 08:18.041
No! Course not!

08:18.090 --> 08:20.001
No. No.

08:20.050 --> 08:21.563
l was married, before...

08:21.610 --> 08:24.443
before Eddie.

08:24.490 --> 08:26.720
Before Eddie...Karen's dad, Eddie?

08:26.770 --> 08:28.806
Yeah, Sheldon.

08:28.850 --> 08:32.604
But he died... of a heart attack.

08:32.650 --> 08:35.448
Oh, well,

08:35.490 --> 08:37.446
you know,

08:37.490 --> 08:39.082
some of these blokes these days

08:39.130 --> 08:40.881
don't take care of themselves,
do they, you know?

08:40.929 --> 08:42.522
No exercise, pissing it up...

08:44.250 --> 08:46.525
But l mean,

08:46.570 --> 08:49.323
if it's putting you off
getting married again, Sheila...

08:49.370 --> 08:50.644
No! No! No, it's not that.

08:52.130 --> 08:53.643
lt's just...

08:53.690 --> 08:55.487
he's buried

08:55.530 --> 08:57.725
in the garden.

09:02.410 --> 09:07.200
You serious?
No coffin, nothing?!

09:08.050 --> 09:10.245
She just wrapped him in a doily,

09:10.290 --> 09:14.203
said a few Hail Marys and
shoved him six feet under.

09:14.250 --> 09:16.844
lt's what he would've wanted,
she reckons.

09:16.890 --> 09:18.960
Give us another pint, Kev,
and a couple of E's.

09:19.010 --> 09:21.649
< lt's a bit fucking weird, though.

09:22.690 --> 09:24.442
Course it's a bit fucking weird!

09:24.490 --> 09:26.845
Fucking Michael Jackson
video in your back garden!

09:26.890 --> 09:29.723
Stiff under the whatsit bush!
lt's hardly Mr And Mrs, is it?

09:29.770 --> 09:32.682
Hey, d'you reckon Karen knows?

09:32.730 --> 09:34.766
Hey, Karen...

09:34.810 --> 09:37.483
Don't tell her, you stupid bastard!

09:37.530 --> 09:39.088
lt's not like he's her dad.

09:39.130 --> 09:41.564
So what did Sheila said about it?
ls she all right?

09:41.610 --> 09:43.566
How the fuck should l know?

09:47.850 --> 09:48.839
Ooh.

09:50.050 --> 09:51.403
Oh.

09:52.010 --> 09:54.922
Hey, hey. So, er... So should
we have heard from the hospital?

09:54.970 --> 09:56.642
Should have been today.

09:56.690 --> 09:58.646
lt might be tomorrow.

09:58.690 --> 10:00.362
l'll take him home, shall l?

10:00.410 --> 10:02.765
Make sure Sheila's all right,
find out what l can.

10:02.810 --> 10:04.687
Come on, tosspot!

10:10.610 --> 10:12.601
Cheers!

10:12.650 --> 10:15.118
Ah, look at that, Liam.
You'd look sweet in that.

10:15.170 --> 10:16.444
Oi!

10:16.490 --> 10:18.845
Who's the - spunk face
- short arse outside?

10:18.890 --> 10:21.643
Who? Oh, not again!

10:21.690 --> 10:23.248
What does he want?

10:23.290 --> 10:24.518
Where?

10:24.570 --> 10:26.879
Ah, go on Debs, he's your
boyfriend, in' he?

10:26.930 --> 10:28.488
You're joking, aren't you?!

10:28.530 --> 10:31.408
He's only about four!
Someone tell him l've gone out.

10:31.450 --> 10:32.439
Come on, Liam.

10:35.610 --> 10:37.680
Fuck off!

10:38.890 --> 10:41.245
Thanks for bringing him home.

10:41.290 --> 10:44.805
Well, l thought l'd come and see
how it's going, you know wi'...

10:44.850 --> 10:45.965
wi' wedding and that.

10:46.010 --> 10:49.764
Sorry l haven't got much to
offer you. l could do you a vodka.

10:49.810 --> 10:51.801
So is that where he's buried, then?

10:51.850 --> 10:53.488
What?!

10:53.530 --> 10:55.248
Oh, l'm.. l'm sorry. lt's just...

10:55.290 --> 10:59.442
Well, Frank said... and,
well... l mean only to us, and l...

10:59.490 --> 11:01.401
What the hell happened?

11:01.450 --> 11:03.441
Oohh.. There's...

11:03.490 --> 11:05.242
Let me, er... Let me do those.

11:05.290 --> 11:08.327
There's not really
much to tell, actually.

11:08.370 --> 11:11.043
l just...couldn't handle
the funeral.

11:11.090 --> 11:12.842
Was the agoraphobia.

11:12.890 --> 11:15.279
And when he fell down stairs
and killed himself,

11:15.330 --> 11:19.243
l thought, the garden's
just as good a place as any.

11:19.290 --> 11:22.566
And he loved that garden,
he loved it.

11:22.610 --> 11:27.559
He used to sit out there
and point where to plant things.

11:27.610 --> 11:31.319
Fell down the stairs?
l... l thought he had a heart attack.

11:31.370 --> 11:35.204
He did. He did. He did,
after he fell down the stairs.

11:35.250 --> 11:38.322
l thought maybe l should've
done him a headstone,

11:38.370 --> 11:40.645
but it would've spoiled
the symmetry.

11:40.690 --> 11:42.521
l mean there wasn't any time.

11:42.570 --> 11:45.960
l didn't even have time to take
off his jewellery.

11:46.010 --> 11:48.080
He didn't like me
to touch him anyway.

11:48.130 --> 11:51.327
That's why l can't wear gold.

11:51.370 --> 11:54.521
That's why l have to
wear fake or platinum. >

11:54.570 --> 11:58.119
Maybe l should have phoned someone
but l knew he was dead because

11:58.170 --> 12:00.047
he didn't get up to watch The Sweeney.

12:00.090 --> 12:02.365
The Sweeney...

12:02.410 --> 12:04.321
What did Frank say? >

12:04.370 --> 12:05.769
What did he say?

12:05.810 --> 12:08.449
How much gold, Sheila?

12:15.530 --> 12:19.523
You look nice, Carol. l always
think animal prints suit you.

12:19.570 --> 12:21.447
Veronica's put you up
to this, hasn't she?

12:21.490 --> 12:22.889
No, of course not.

12:22.930 --> 12:25.524
Hmm. Well, whatever it is
you're wanting, l'm not biting.

12:25.570 --> 12:27.367
Hiya, Debbie. >

12:27.410 --> 12:33.280
Doing a good trade on the confetti.
Waste not, fucking want not.

12:35.250 --> 12:40.483
The thing is, it's not actually
me wanting something. lt's Sheila.

12:40.530 --> 12:45.558
She's stressed about the wedding and
she wants me to be her bridesmaid but...

12:45.610 --> 12:47.089
The answer's no.

12:47.130 --> 12:49.325
Oh, go on, Carol, please.

12:49.370 --> 12:51.281
l'm not nicking you a dress.

12:51.330 --> 12:53.605
l got cautioned the last time. >

12:53.650 --> 12:55.880
l can't take that chance again.

12:58.010 --> 13:00.843
All right, Yvonne?
Just a pack of gum for me.

13:01.810 --> 13:02.845
3.20.

13:02.890 --> 13:06.280
Take What You Want Day for
bearded ladies were last week, Carol.

13:12.410 --> 13:13.729
Thank you.

13:18.410 --> 13:20.480
Why are you following me?

13:20.530 --> 13:23.567
l've got Racing Ninjas.

13:23.610 --> 13:25.487
Look, Brian, the thing is...

13:25.530 --> 13:28.363
l don't want to be rude or anything.

13:28.410 --> 13:30.241
l'm just not really interested.

13:30.290 --> 13:33.282
lt's nothing personal or anything.
lt's just...

13:33.330 --> 13:36.845
lt's all about chemicals in your
brain and you can't help those -

13:36.890 --> 13:39.404
who you've got them for
and who you haven't.

13:39.450 --> 13:42.283
And with you, l just haven't.

13:42.330 --> 13:45.800
Sorry. No hard feelings, eh?

13:45.850 --> 13:49.399
You can have me skateboard
if you let me kiss ya.

13:51.130 --> 13:53.007
l don't want a skateboard.

13:54.050 --> 13:56.803
What l want is a bridesmaid dress.

14:00.490 --> 14:01.969
Frank? Frank!

14:05.850 --> 14:07.568
What d'ya do that for?!

14:07.610 --> 14:09.919
She's buried him with a load of gold!

14:09.970 --> 14:12.643
He was covered in it!
Rings, watches, teeth.

14:12.690 --> 14:14.521
Must be worth a fortune.

14:16.210 --> 14:18.280
What the fuck's
that gotta do wi' me?

14:18.330 --> 14:20.048
We need to dig him up!

14:20.090 --> 14:22.206
Dig? Are you off your f...
Dig him up?!

14:22.250 --> 14:25.162
lt's not Brookside.
He's a dead person!

14:25.210 --> 14:27.849
Well, exactly!
He don't need it, does he, eh?

14:27.890 --> 14:30.802
lt were years ago.
He'll only be a bag of bones.

14:30.850 --> 14:35.162
Oh, and what? You don't think
he's entitled to everlasting...

14:35.210 --> 14:36.962
you know, fucking whatsit?

14:37.010 --> 14:39.968
A man's soul's has a right to
be left in peace, doesn't he,

14:40.010 --> 14:41.602
or what is the world coming to?

14:41.650 --> 14:44.881
You can say a few prayers
when you bury him again.

14:46.450 --> 14:48.884
Come on, Frank.

14:48.930 --> 14:50.568
Kev's cousin can fence it.

14:50.610 --> 14:52.282
All we need to do

14:52.330 --> 14:57.563
is get rid of Sheila for the night,
dig him up, split it 50/50.

14:57.610 --> 14:59.123
lt's yours by rights.

14:59.170 --> 15:01.843
Yeah, but... ls it?

15:01.890 --> 15:06.566
Yeah, course it is! Cos...well,
Sheldon were married to Sheila...

15:06.610 --> 15:07.201
Yeah..

15:07.250 --> 15:09.127
..which makes her his next of kin...

15:09.170 --> 15:11.843
..you're married to Sheila...

15:11.890 --> 15:15.678
Well, near enough,
so that makes you her...

15:15.730 --> 15:17.686
l really need this money, Frank!

15:17.730 --> 15:19.448
And don't pretend you don't.

15:19.490 --> 15:23.199
Money Sheila's spending on
this wedding. lt's payback.

15:23.250 --> 15:26.765
That's better. Ooh, you're awake.

15:27.530 --> 15:28.724
Oh...

15:49.530 --> 15:51.646
That was a bit hardcore.

15:52.730 --> 15:54.322
What time is it?

15:54.370 --> 15:56.088
'Bout three.

